{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1111,"text":"Today, I am going to talk about anger.\n"},{"time":9128,"text":"When I was 11,"},{"time":11130,"text":"seeing some of my friends \nleaving the school"},{"time":14462,"text":"because their parents \ncould not afford textbooks"},{"time":18684,"text":"made me angry."},{"time":23316,"text":"When I was 27,"},{"time":26068,"text":"hearing the plight\nof a desperate slave father"},{"time":31280,"text":"whose daughter was \nabout to be sold to a brothel"},{"time":36302,"text":"made me angry."},{"time":40423,"text":"At the age of 50,"},{"time":42763,"text":"lying on the street,\nin a pool of blood,"},{"time":47586,"text":"along with my own son,"},{"time":50532,"text":"made me angry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55299,"text":"Dear friends, for centuries\nwe were taught anger is bad."},{"time":61274,"text":"Our parents, teachers, priests --"},{"time":63486,"text":"everyone taught us how to control \nand suppress our anger."},{"time":72241,"text":"But I ask why?"},{"time":75596,"text":"Why can't we convert our anger\nfor the larger good of society?"},{"time":80513,"text":"Why can't we use our anger"},{"time":82109,"text":"to challenge and change\nthe evils of the world?"},{"time":89705,"text":"That I tried to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94036,"text":"Friends,"},{"time":97367,"text":"most of the brightest ideas\ncame to my mind out of anger."},{"time":103814,"text":"Like when I was 35 and sat \nin a locked-up, tiny prison."},{"time":114564,"text":"The whole night, I was angry."},{"time":117957,"text":"But it has given birth to a new idea."},{"time":121017,"text":"But I will come to that later on."},{"time":124176,"text":"Let me begin with the story\nof how I got a name for myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133481,"text":"I had been a big admirer \nof Mahatma Gandhi since my childhood."},{"time":139032,"text":"Gandhi fought and lead \nIndia's freedom movement."},{"time":145261,"text":"But more importantly,"},{"time":147299,"text":"he taught us how to treat \nthe most vulnerable sections,"},{"time":154034,"text":"the most deprived people, \nwith dignity and respect."},{"time":159595,"text":"And so, when India was celebrating"},{"time":164562,"text":"Mahatma Gandhi's \nbirth centenary in 1969 --"},{"time":167829,"text":"at that time I was 15 --"},{"time":170117,"text":"an idea came to my mind."},{"time":173774,"text":"Why can't we celebrate it differently?"},{"time":177244,"text":"I knew, as perhaps\nmany of you might know,"},{"time":182672,"text":"that in India, a large number of people\nare born in the lowest segment of caste."},{"time":192185,"text":"And they are treated as untouchables."},{"time":195324,"text":"These are the people --"},{"time":196656,"text":"forget about allowing them \nto go to the temples,"},{"time":201066,"text":"they cannot even go into the houses \nand shops of high-caste people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208250,"text":"So I was very impressed with \nthe leaders of my town"},{"time":213564,"text":"who were speaking very highly against\nthe caste system and untouchability"},{"time":218102,"text":"and talking of Gandhian ideals."},{"time":221774,"text":"So inspired by that, I thought,\nlet us set an example"},{"time":224944,"text":"by inviting these people to eat food\ncooked and served"},{"time":231389,"text":"by the untouchable community."},{"time":234619,"text":"I went to some low-caste,\nso-called untouchable, people,"},{"time":241421,"text":"tried to convince them,\nbut it was unthinkable for them."},{"time":245807,"text":"They told me, \"No, no. It's not possible.\nIt never happened.\""},{"time":251070,"text":"I said, \"Look at these leaders,"},{"time":252784,"text":"they are so great, \nthey are against untouchability."},{"time":255221,"text":"They will come. If nobody comes, \nwe can set an example.\""},{"time":260891,"text":"These people thought that I was too naive."},{"time":268161,"text":"Finally, they were convinced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270651,"text":"My friends and I took our bicycles\nand invited political leaders."},{"time":277982,"text":"And I was so thrilled, rather, empowered"},{"time":281126,"text":"to see that each one of them \nagreed to come."},{"time":287192,"text":"I thought, \"Great idea.\nWe can set an example."},{"time":290083,"text":"We can bring about change in the society.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":295451,"text":"The day has come."},{"time":297724,"text":"All these untouchables,\nthree women and two men,"},{"time":303467,"text":"they agreed to come."},{"time":307436,"text":"I could recall that they had used \nthe best of their clothes."},{"time":314475,"text":"They brought new utensils."},{"time":318000,"text":"They had taken baths \nhundreds of times"},{"time":320339,"text":"because it was unthinkable\nfor them to do."},{"time":323300,"text":"It was the moment of change."},{"time":327254,"text":"They gathered. Food was cooked."},{"time":330402,"text":"It was 7 o'clock."},{"time":333000,"text":"By 8 o'clock, we kept on waiting,"},{"time":335876,"text":"because it's not very uncommon \nthat the leaders become late,"},{"time":340857,"text":"for an hour or so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343239,"text":"So after 8 o'clock, we took our bicycles\nand went to these leaders' homes,"},{"time":349922,"text":"just to remind them."},{"time":354248,"text":"One of the leader's wives told me,"},{"time":358945,"text":"\"Sorry, he is having some headache,\nperhaps he cannot come.\""},{"time":363960,"text":"I went to another leader"},{"time":366037,"text":"and his wife told me, \n\"Okay, you go, he will definitely join.\""},{"time":371357,"text":"So I thought that the dinner\nwill take place,"},{"time":375469,"text":"though not at that large a scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381352,"text":"I went back to the venue, which was\na newly built Mahatma Gandhi Park."},{"time":388559,"text":"It was 10 o'clock."},{"time":391483,"text":"None of the leaders showed up."},{"time":396132,"text":"That made me angry."},{"time":400275,"text":"I was standing, leaning against\nMahatma Gandhi's statue."},{"time":409839,"text":"I was emotionally drained,\nrather exhausted."},{"time":416890,"text":"Then I sat down where \nthe food was lying."},{"time":425695,"text":"I kept my emotions on hold."},{"time":427785,"text":"But then, when I took the first bite,"},{"time":432279,"text":"I broke down in tears."},{"time":435210,"text":"And suddenly I felt a hand on my shoulder."},{"time":440149,"text":"And it was the healing, motherly touch \nof an untouchable woman."},{"time":446047,"text":"And she told me,\n\"Kailash, why are you crying?"},{"time":451598,"text":"You have done your bit."},{"time":454011,"text":"You have eaten the food\ncooked by untouchables,"},{"time":457136,"text":"which has never happened in our memory.\""},{"time":461207,"text":"She said, \"You won today.\""},{"time":465789,"text":"And my friends, she was right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472059,"text":"I came back home, a little after midnight,"},{"time":475789,"text":"shocked to see that several \nhigh-caste elderly people"},{"time":480363,"text":"were sitting in my courtyard."},{"time":482517,"text":"I saw my mother and \nelderly women were crying"},{"time":485613,"text":"and they were pleading \nto these elderly people"},{"time":490071,"text":"because they had threatened \nto outcaste my whole family."},{"time":494345,"text":"And you know, outcasting the family\nis the biggest social punishment"},{"time":499477,"text":"one can think of."},{"time":503981,"text":"Somehow they agreed to punish only me,\nand the punishment was purification."},{"time":508821,"text":"That means I had to go 600 miles\naway from my hometown"},{"time":513336,"text":"to the River Ganges to take a holy dip."},{"time":517267,"text":"And after that, I should organize a feast\nfor priests, 101 priests,"},{"time":521691,"text":"wash their feet and drink that water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526529,"text":"It was total nonsense,"},{"time":529528,"text":"and I refused to accept that punishment."},{"time":533267,"text":"How did they punish me?"},{"time":535397,"text":"I was barred from entering into my own \nkitchen and my own dining room,"},{"time":541194,"text":"my utensils were separated."},{"time":544246,"text":"But the night when I was angry,\nthey wanted to outcaste me."},{"time":550600,"text":"But I decided to outcaste \nthe entire caste system."},{"time":555503,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":560988,"text":"And that was possible because\nthe beginning would have been"},{"time":566003,"text":"to change the family name, or surname,"},{"time":568119,"text":"because in India, most of\nthe family names are caste names."},{"time":571784,"text":"So I decided to drop my name."},{"time":574306,"text":"And then, later on, I gave \na new name to myself: Satyarthi,"},{"time":580810,"text":"that means, \"seeker of truth.\""},{"time":585216,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":589248,"text":"And that was the beginning \nof my transformative anger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594095,"text":"Friends, maybe one of you can tell me,"},{"time":596704,"text":"what was I doing before becoming\na children's rights activist?"},{"time":602410,"text":"Does anybody know?"},{"time":604898,"text":"No."},{"time":606169,"text":"I was an engineer, an electrical engineer."},{"time":612558,"text":"And then I learned how the energy"},{"time":617662,"text":"of burning fire, coal,"},{"time":622146,"text":"the nuclear blast inside the chambers,"},{"time":626250,"text":"raging river currents,"},{"time":629442,"text":"fierce winds,"},{"time":633066,"text":"could be converted into the light \nand lives of millions."},{"time":638963,"text":"I also learned how the most\nuncontrollable form of energy"},{"time":643495,"text":"could be harnessed for good \nand making society better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652925,"text":"So I'll come back to the story\nof when I was caught in the prison:"},{"time":659692,"text":"I was very happy freeing \na dozen children from slavery,"},{"time":663919,"text":"handing them over to their parents."},{"time":666890,"text":"I cannot explain my joy \nwhen I free a child."},{"time":671238,"text":"I was so happy."},{"time":673458,"text":"But when I was waiting for my train\nto come back to my hometown, Delhi,"},{"time":679021,"text":"I saw that dozens of children \nwere arriving;"},{"time":682264,"text":"they were being trafficked by someone."},{"time":685562,"text":"I stopped them, those people."},{"time":688415,"text":"I complained to the police."},{"time":690517,"text":"So the policemen, instead of helping me,"},{"time":695071,"text":"they threw me in this small, \ntiny shell, like an animal."},{"time":701573,"text":"And that was the night of anger"},{"time":703121,"text":"when one of the brightest \nand biggest ideas was born."},{"time":707632,"text":"I thought that if I keep on freeing 10 \nchildren, and 50 more will join,"},{"time":713100,"text":"that's not done."},{"time":714560,"text":"And I believed in the power of consumers,"},{"time":717368,"text":"and let me tell you that this\nwas the first time"},{"time":720852,"text":"when a campaign was launched by me\nor anywhere in the world,"},{"time":725968,"text":"to educate and sensitize the consumers\n"},{"time":730041,"text":"to create a demand\nfor child-labor-free rugs."},{"time":735691,"text":"In Europe and America, \nwe have been successful."},{"time":739083,"text":"And it has resulted \nin a fall in child labor"},{"time":743768,"text":"in South Asian countries by 80 percent."},{"time":747024,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":752736,"text":"Not only that, but this first-ever \nconsumer's power, or consumer's campaign"},{"time":759397,"text":"has grown in other countries\nand other industries,"},{"time":763505,"text":"maybe chocolate, maybe apparel, \nmaybe shoes -- it has gone beyond."},{"time":771271,"text":"My anger at the age of 11,"},{"time":772823,"text":"when I realized how important\neducation is for every child,"},{"time":778176,"text":"I got an idea to collect used books\nand help the poorest children."},{"time":785821,"text":"I created a book bank at the age of 11."},{"time":790570,"text":"But I did not stop."},{"time":791813,"text":"Later on, I cofounded"},{"time":794046,"text":"the world's single largest civil society\ncampaign for education"},{"time":798580,"text":"that is the Global Campaign for Education."},{"time":802221,"text":"That has helped in changing \nthe whole thinking towards education"},{"time":806866,"text":"from the charity mode\nto the human rights mode,"},{"time":809257,"text":"and that has concretely helped \nthe reduction of out-of-school children"},{"time":814026,"text":"by half in the last 15 years."},{"time":817614,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":823753,"text":"My anger at the age of 27,"},{"time":826867,"text":"to free that girl who was about\nto be sold to a brothel,"},{"time":832235,"text":"has given me an idea"},{"time":837018,"text":"to go for a new strategy\nof raid and rescue,"},{"time":841271,"text":"freeing children from slavery."},{"time":844758,"text":"And I am so lucky and proud to say\nthat it is not one or 10 or 20,"},{"time":850614,"text":"but my colleagues and I have been able\nto physically liberate 83,000 child slaves"},{"time":856962,"text":"and hand them over\nback to their families and mothers."},{"time":860093,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":865692,"text":"I knew that we needed global policies."},{"time":867979,"text":"We organized the worldwide marches\nagainst child labor"},{"time":871011,"text":"and that has also resulted in \na new international convention"},{"time":877073,"text":"to protect the children\nwho are in the worst forms."},{"time":882262,"text":"And the concrete result was that\nthe number of child laborers globally"},{"time":886351,"text":"has gone down by one third \nin the last 15 years."},{"time":891891,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":896311,"text":"So, in each case,"},{"time":899721,"text":"it began from anger,"},{"time":903510,"text":"turned into an idea,"},{"time":906159,"text":"and action."},{"time":909565,"text":"So anger, what next?"},{"time":912441,"text":"Idea, and --"},{"time":914920,"text":"Audience: Action"},{"time":916278,"text":"Kailash Satyarthi: Anger, idea, action.\nWhich I tried to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922254,"text":"Anger is a power, anger is an energy,"},{"time":924751,"text":"and the law of nature is that energy"},{"time":927552,"text":"can never be created and never \nbe vanished, can never be destroyed."},{"time":932795,"text":"So why can't the energy of anger\nbe translated and harnessed"},{"time":939685,"text":"to create a better and beautiful world,\na more just and equitable world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":944861,"text":"Anger is within each one of you,"},{"time":947341,"text":"and I will share a secret\nfor a few seconds:"},{"time":953241,"text":"that if we are confined in \nthe narrow shells of egos,"},{"time":960795,"text":"and the circles of selfishness,"},{"time":965225,"text":"then the anger will turn out to be\nhatred, violence, revenge, destruction."},{"time":973539,"text":"But if we are able to break the circles,"},{"time":976595,"text":"then the same anger could turn \ninto a great power."},{"time":982481,"text":"We can break the circles \nby using our inherent compassion"},{"time":986828,"text":"and connect with the world through \ncompassion to make this world better."},{"time":990678,"text":"That same anger could be\ntransformed into it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994351,"text":"So dear friends, sisters and brothers,\nagain, as a Nobel Laureate,"},{"time":999956,"text":"I am urging you to become angry."},{"time":1003841,"text":"I am urging you to become angry."},{"time":1008003,"text":"And the angriest among us"},{"time":1012299,"text":"is the one who can transform his anger \ninto idea and action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020440,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022275,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1035115,"text":"Chris Anderson: For many years, \nyou've been an inspiration to others."},{"time":1038924,"text":"Who or what inspires you and why?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042629,"text":"KS: Good question."},{"time":1044341,"text":"Chris, let me tell you, \nand that is the truth,"},{"time":1048335,"text":"each time when I free a child,"},{"time":1052849,"text":"the child who has lost all his hope\nthat he will ever come back to his mother,"},{"time":1057028,"text":"the first smile of freedom,"},{"time":1061335,"text":"and the mother who has lost all hope"},{"time":1063890,"text":"that the son or daughter \ncan ever come back and sit in her lap,"},{"time":1070501,"text":"they become so emotional"},{"time":1072656,"text":"and the first tear of joy \nrolls down on her cheek,"},{"time":1077809,"text":"I see the glimpse of God in it --\nthis is my biggest inspiration."},{"time":1081154,"text":"And I am so lucky that not once,\nas I said before, but thousands of times,"},{"time":1086032,"text":"I have been able to witness my God\nin the faces of those children"},{"time":1089628,"text":"and they are my biggest inspirations."},{"time":1091640,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1093652,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}